## 2) While working — migration awareness

If the slice changes **stored ladder truth** (new DB column/table/index, `scripts/ladder/`, per-game or periodic writers): note that `docs/UPDATE_DOCS.md` Part B will apply at wrap-up. Do not block vibecoding to fill registers mid-flight unless Dagh asks.

### Performance-first stored truth

For DB-backed website features, especially profile, status, activity, leaderboards, achievements, and fun stats, **the default path is stored/precomputed truth, not live historical aggregation.**

**Empirical evidence (May 2026):** A daily-active-players chart reading a tiny precomputed table measured **73× faster** than computing the same value from `ratedresults` on the fly (~21 ms vs ~1,542 ms query time), even though `ratedresults` has only ~75k rows. Row count alone is a bad predictor of cost on this table because it is wide (27 columns, `mediumtext` fields), two-player games require `UNION ALL` doubling to ~150k row-reads, and `COUNT(DISTINCT)` per group is expensive. **Do not assume "the table is small, a live scan is fine."**

**Default:** Any feature that aggregates across historical `ratedresults` rows — games per day, active players per period, milestone counts, cumulative stats, leaderboard snapshots — should store the result in an aggregate table, rebuild it once from history, and maintain it post-game. Raw aggregation from `ratedresults` is acceptable only for:

- Throwaway/exploratory probes (`scripts/` one-offs)
- Narrow single-player lookups that use `idA`/`idB` indexes
- Genuinely temporary prototypes you plan to replace

Do **not** block PHP ops, contract, schema, replay, index, aggregate-table, or periodic-job work merely because Steve coordination or register handoff is needed later. **Do not extend legacy C++ derived post-game** — implement and prove in **`site/public_html/ops/`** per [`docs/ladder-ops-platform.md`](docs/ladder-ops-platform.md) §2.

### Ladder ops — no `staging-scripts/`

**`site/public_html/staging-scripts/` was removed Jun 2026.** Do not recreate it or “fix bugs” in deleted cutover runners. Server ladder work = **`site/public_html/ops/`** only (`run_prepare.php`, `run_process_game.php`, `run_ops_sim.php`, `dispatch.php`, …). Local batch repair / parity = `scripts/ladder/`, `scripts/work_prepare/`, `scripts/rebuild_website_derived_data_local.ps1` (Mode B, not live path). See [`docs/archive/staging-scripts-inventory.md`](docs/archive/staging-scripts-inventory.md).

**Cutover vocabulary:** Prep is **done** on `kooldb1` via ops simul; live prod is Steve’s scheduled cutover; batch `*_rebuild.sql` and `rebuild_website_derived_data_local.ps1` are **legacy repair on `ko2unity_db` only** — not tasks, not prod. Read [`docs/coordination/cutover-readiness.md`](docs/coordination/cutover-readiness.md) before assigning “pending on prod” work.

**Work DB hygiene (`ko2unity_work` / `kooldb1`):** Sign-off = **`zero-derived` → `run_ops_sim.php` → `verify` only.** Wrong derived state after a writer fix → re-simul, not batch repair (`rebuild-all`, ad-hoc SQL, repair verbs). [`docs/work-db-prepare.md`](docs/work-db-prepare.md) §1.5. CLI refuses `rebuild-all` on work targets.

Default question before implementing stats: *What stored table should this value live in, and what does `docs/website-data-contract.md` say for rebuild and post-game?* — not "can we compute it on the fly?" Do not create or cite `PG-00x` / `cpp-snippets/`. Work/staging proof = **ops simul** (`run_ops_sim.php` + verify); batch SQL in `scripts/ladder/sql/archive/` = repair/oracle only.

Use read-time SQL only when it is clearly cheap (single-row lookup, indexed narrow fetch), infrequent (admin-only, one-off), or the value genuinely cannot be precomputed (depends on request-time parameters that are unbounded).

