## 3) When to run “finish” (UPDATE_DOCS) — same turn as “done”

**Dagh may close the chat without saying goodbye.** There is no signal when a chat is archived. If you wait for “update docs” or “we’re done”, docs may never get updated.

**Therefore — run finish in the same assistant turn where you deliver completed work**, not in a later turn Dagh might never trigger.

### Run Part A (+ Part B if needed) when ANY of these is true:

1. You just implemented what the user asked for in this thread (feature/fix slice complete).
2. User says **update docs**, **done**, **ship it**, **that’s all**, or similar.
3. User approves your plan and you execute it in one go — update docs **after** the code, same reply.

### Do NOT wait for:

- A follow-up message
- User saying “finish”
- User closing the chat (you will not see that)

### In that same reply, order:

1. Do the code/docs file edits for the feature.
2. Run **`docs/UPDATE_DOCS.md`** Part A (MEMORY line, specs, feature-log).
3. Part B only if migration triggers.
4. Tell Dagh in one line what you recorded (e.g. “MEMORY + STATUS_PAGE_DATA updated”).

### Skip or defer Part A only if:

- User explicitly said **WIP**, **pause**, **don’t update docs yet**, or only asked a question (no implementation).
- You are mid-plan and have not written shipping code yet.

Cosmetics-only slice: Part A only; skip Part B registers.

